From: VXA17 Kernel Team
Date: Sun Jul 19 2026
Subject: [PATCH] PMI632: Dynamically force flash boost on FLASH_ACTIVE

Instead of a one-time init choice between FIXED_MODE (torch works,
charging dead) and ADAPTIVE_MODE (charging works, torch dead),
dynamically toggle FORCE_FLASH_BOOST_5V_BIT and TORCH_PRIORITY_CONTROL_BIT
when the camera framework sets FLASH_ACTIVE.

This allows:
- Torch ON  → boost forced → physical LED works (USB charging suspended)
- Torch OFF → boost released → USB charging resumes immediately

DTB must set qcom,headroom-mode = <1> (ADAPTIVE_MODE) so init doesn't
permanently force boost.

Signed-off-by: VXA17 Kernel Team
---
 drivers/power/supply/qcom/schgm-flash.h  |  1 +
 drivers/power/supply/qcom/schgm-flash.c  | 28 +++++++++++++++++++++++
 drivers/power/supply/qcom/qpnp-smb5.c    |  2 ++
 3 files changed, 31 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/power/supply/qcom/schgm-flash.h b/drivers/power/supply/qcom/schgm-flash.h
index d1aab2a6f9f2..25fb027f4c29 100644
--- a/drivers/power/supply/qcom/schgm-flash.h
+++ b/drivers/power/supply/qcom/schgm-flash.h
@@ -50,4 +50,5 @@ irqreturn_t schgm_flash_default_irq_handler(int irq, void *data);
 irqreturn_t schgm_flash_ilim2_irq_handler(int irq, void *data);
 irqreturn_t schgm_flash_state_change_irq_handler(int irq, void *data);
+void schgm_flash_set_active(struct smb_charger *chg, bool active);
 #endif /* __SCHGM_FLASH_H__ */
diff --git a/drivers/power/supply/qcom/schgm-flash.c b/drivers/power/supply/qcom/schgm-flash.c
index e7db426c3830..233e6c2bcee1 100644
--- a/drivers/power/supply/qcom/schgm-flash.c
+++ b/drivers/power/supply/qcom/schgm-flash.c
@@ -97,6 +97,34 @@ bool is_flash_active(struct smb_charger *chg)
 	return chg->flash_active ? true : false;
 }
 
+void schgm_flash_set_active(struct smb_charger *chg, bool active)
+{
+	int rc;
+	u8 reg;
+
+	reg = active ? FORCE_FLASH_BOOST_5V_BIT : 0;
+	rc = smblib_masked_write(chg, SCHGM_FORCE_BOOST_CONTROL,
+			FORCE_FLASH_BOOST_5V_BIT, reg);
+	if (rc < 0) {
+		pr_err("Couldn't %s flash boost rc=%d\n",
+			active ? "force" : "release", rc);
+		return;
+	}
+
+	reg = active ? TORCH_PRIORITY_CONTROL_BIT : 0;
+	rc = smblib_masked_write(chg, SCHGM_TORCH_PRIORITY_CONTROL_REG,
+			TORCH_PRIORITY_CONTROL_BIT, reg);
+	if (rc < 0) {
+		pr_err("Couldn't %s torch priority rc=%d\n",
+			active ? "set" : "clear", rc);
+		return;
+	}
+
+	pr_debug("flash active=%d boost=%s\n", active,
+		active ? "forced 5V" : "adaptive");
+}
+EXPORT_SYMBOL(schgm_flash_set_active);
+
 int schgm_flash_get_vreg_ok(struct smb_charger *chg, int *val)
 {
 	int rc, vreg_state;
diff --git a/drivers/power/supply/qcom/qpnp-smb5.c b/drivers/power/supply/qcom/qpnp-smb5.c
index 8e33f05bf6a0..44b4869ad1c9 100644
--- a/drivers/power/supply/qcom/qpnp-smb5.c
+++ b/drivers/power/supply/qcom/qpnp-smb5.c
@@ -1452,6 +1452,8 @@ static int smb5_set_prop(struct smb_charger *chg, enum power_supply_property psp
 		if ((chg->chg_param.smb_version == PMI632_SUBTYPE)
 				&& (chg->flash_active != val->intval)) {
 			chg->flash_active = val->intval;
+
+			schgm_flash_set_active(chg, !!chg->flash_active);
 
 			rc = smblib_get_prop_usb_present(chg, &pval);
 			if (rc < 0)
